def draw_a_plot(dimension, function, xlabel, func_label, dimension_label):

    users.groupby(dimension)[['assembly_shop', 'research_center', 'spaceport', 'total_bildings']] \
         .agg(function) \
         .plot(figsize=(9, 4),
               kind='bar',
               grid=True,
               title=(func_label + '    \n    ' + dimension_label),
               xlabel=xlabel,
               ylabel=' ',
               rot=0);

In[43]:
def get_metrics(users, dimensions=[]):
    
    revenue = users.pivot_table(index=dimensions,
                                columns='lifetime',
                                values='total_bildings',
                                aggfunc='sum')
    revenue = revenue.fillna(0).cumsum(axis=1)
    cohort_sizes = users.groupby(dimensions, as_index=False)['user_id'].nunique() \
                        .rename(columns={'user_id': 'cohort_size'})
    revenue = cohort_sizes.merge(revenue, on=dimensions, how='left').fillna(0)
    revenue = revenue.set_index(dimensions)
    
    ltv = revenue.div(revenue['cohort_size'], axis=0)
    ltv = ltv.drop(columns=['cohort_size'])

    cac = users[['user_id', 'cac'] + dimensions]
    cac = cac.groupby(dimensions).mean()
    
    roi = cac.merge(ltv, left_index=True, right_index=True)
    roi = roi.div(roi['cac'], axis=0).drop(columns=['cac'])
    
    return ltv, roi
